      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PASSION AND PAIN (6) drew wide and had to work so was brave when boxing in for fifth in the Listed Sapling Stakes at Menangle last start. Was very good in his other two starts at this circuit and distance, coming from wider for a debut second before winning the Sapling Final. Talented and will take beating. BETTOR ELEMENTS (7) made a strong start to his career when he scored by 3 metres at Penrith. Tactics will be crucial from this wide draw but he has upside. Darren Elder's debutant BUCKAROO SHANNON (1) won his latest trial and is aided by the ace draw so keep safe. PLAYBOY ROCKY (4) only beat one home when he debuted from a wider barrier in the Sapling Stakes at Menangle but should find this easier.",
